data.title: Sigma: The Equation to the Grand Finals
data.description: With Sigma propelling his way into the 2019 Overwatch League playoffs, Vancouver has seen some significant changes in their play except for big one: winning. Twilight and Tizi discuss the reforms to the Titans lineup and how they aren’t phased when it comes to change.

data.title: Best of the 2019 Overwatch League
data.description: Relive the best moments from an amazing 2019 Overwatch League season. From thrilling victories, devastating defeats, crazy comebacks, and moments that make your jaw drop, the 2019 season has been quite the ride.

data.title: Tactics: Executing High-Damage Sigma Combos
data.description: Sigma was introduced to the Overwatch League during the 2019 Playoffs and he had a huge impact on the meta! His abilities, Accretion and Gravitic Flux, offer strong crowd-control capabilities that can be used to set up high-damage combos. In this episode of Tactics, we break down three different big combos that Sigma can execute with some help from his teammates. It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Re-Fusion: Philadelphia Swings for the Grand Finals
data.description: Watching London hold the trophy above their heads at the Inaugural season’s Grand Finals was tough for the Philadelphia Fusion. Poko, Carpe and EQO want to let the league know they won’t let history repeat itself and they intend to make it to the Grand Finals for their hometown crowd.

data.title: Meta Report: Stage 4
data.description: The 2-2-2 role lock had a huge impact on the Overwatch League Stage 4 meta! Join Soe, Malik, Bren, Wolf, and Achilios as they walk us through the biggest changes we've seen in this new meta and the teams and players who have found new life! It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: London Spitfire: Repeat Quest?
data.description: History was captured last year when the London Spitfire took home the Inaugural Season Overwatch League trophy. Can they re-capture history? They’ll have to fight out of the play-in bracket first.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The Vancouver Titans
data.description: Join us as your bard Seth “Achilios” King recounts the tale of the mighty Vancouver Titans and how they were able to utterly dominate the regular season and brute their way to the 2019 season Overwatch League season playoffs.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The New York Excelsior
data.description: Join us for another installment of MasterPath Theatre as Erik “Doa” Lonnquist tells the tale of the mighty New York Excelsior and their quest for championship glory in the 2019 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The San Francisco Shock
data.description: Come take a seat around the fire as Mitch "Uber" Leslie regales us with the tale of the San Francisco Shock's epic path to the playoffs in this edition of MasterPath Theatre.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The Atlanta Reign
data.description: It’s a fireside chat with our pal Semmler, who chronicles the Atlanta Reigns rise from the ashes to the Overwatch League Playoffs. As they say… Let’s go, dude.

data.title: Tactics: How Surefour's Hanzo Shut Down the Los Angeles Valiant
data.description: The Los Angeles Valiant were battling the Los Angeles Gladiators on Volskaya Industries. The LA Valiant had to capture 80% of Point B with less than a minute remaining and they had a decent shot at doing it. However, Surefour dismantled the last two pushes of the Los Angeles Valiant. In this episode of Tactics, we break down just how Surefour managed to find those key headshots and how the Los Angeles Valiant failed to mitigate that risk for themselves! It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.
